    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine sancte et individue Trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/239">Otto</persName>, divina favente clemencia, <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus. Si ea, que sanctis iniuste
                        sunt ablata restituerimus, ad salutem nostre anime provenire non diffidimus.
                        Quapropter omnium fidelium sancte Dei Ecclesie, nostrorumque presencium, ac
                        futurorum comperiat universitas [...] <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >monasterium</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Monasteries #Abbots #Muslims #Rivers #Riverbed #Animals #Wine #Hay/fodder #Fish #Fisheries #Forests #Mills #Cells/hermitages #Churches #Landed_possessions #Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1900">Sancti Vincencii</orgName>
                        <persName key="#Abbots" ref="#people/1966">Iohannes</persName> venerabilis
                            <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs>, nostram adiens clemenciam, conqueri et
                        reclamare ceperat, quod monasterium Sancti Vincencii destructum a nefanda
                        gente <rs key="#Muslims">Agarenorum</rs>, pene omnibus destitutum rebus, et
                        ab inimicis Dei ecclesiarum Dei contrarii iniuste retineri nostris
                        temporibus videtur. Scilicet <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/1939">Sancti
                            Donati</orgName>; et <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterium</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/1938">Sancte
                            Columbe</orgName> et <orgName key="#Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1998">Sancto Marciano</orgName>: 
                        
                        ab una parte
                        fine Acerno; ab alia parte fine Fossato; alio capite fine <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1999">Sancta Iusta</orgName>; et ab alio capite
                        coniunctum est cum ipso monasterio de Sancta Columba; 
                        
                        simulque <rs
                            key="#Cells/hermitages">cella</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/2300">Sancti
                            Iuliani</orgName> de <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#places/2000">Vico Albo</placeName>: 
                        
                        ab una parte <rs
                            key="#Rivers #Cells/hermitages">rivus</rs>, qui pergit per vallem de
                            <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/2820">Castagnetum</placeName>; ab
                        alia parte <rs key="#Rivers">rivus</rs>, qui dicitur de Mala Fide; ab alia
                        parte <rs key="#Roads">via puplica</rs>, que venit ad Sanctam Mariam; et ab
                        alio capite rivus, qui venit ad fontem Vetula, 
                        
                        <rs key="#Curtes">curtem</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Curtes" ref="#estates/1932">Sancti Casti et Sancte
                            Marie</geogName>, que sunt ad Sanctum Georgium fine fonte Karoli et
                        fine valle de Vicu, quomodo in <placeName ref="#places/2821"
                            >Rosanisco</placeName> vadit 
                        
                        et <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/1941"
                            >Sanctum Maurum</orgName> de <placeName ref="#places/2360"
                            >Anglone</placeName> cum pertinenciis suis; 
                        
                        simulque <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">campum</rs> Borrani qui dicitur, qui habet
                        finis: ab una parte <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terra</rs>
                        <persName key="#Landed_possessions"><name ref="Richardus"
                            >Richardi</name></persName>; ad alia parte <rs key="#Roads">via
                            puplica</rs>; a tercia parte fine <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >terra</rs>
                        <persName key="#Landed_possessions"><name ref="Adelbertus Sabinianus"
                                >Adelberti</name></persName>, qui Sabinianus vocatur; quarta pars
                        fine <persName key="#Landed_possessions">terra</persName>
                        <orgName key="#Landed_possessions" ref="#juridical_persons/1994">Sancti
                            Angeli</orgName> de <placeName ref="#places/2311">Barregio</placeName>;
                        
                        
                       in valle, que dicitur <placeName key="#Churches #Landed_possessions" ref="#places/2819"
                            >Sorana</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Churches">ecclesiam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Churches #Landed_possessions" ref="#juridical_persons/2301">
                            Sancti Stephani</orgName> cum omnibus suis
                        <rs key="#Landed_possessions">pertinenciis</rs>; 
                        
                        
                        preterea in <rs key="#Actio">actu</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Churches #Actio #Churches #Rivers #Castle"
                            ref="#estates/313">Balvense</geogName>, in loco qui nuncupatur
                        <placeName key="#Churches #Landed_possessions #Rivers #Castle" ref="#places/2815">Quinque
                            Milia</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Churches">ecclesiam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Churches #Landed_possessions" ref="#juridical_persons/1996">Sancte
                            Marie</orgName>, que cella eiusdem monasterii dinoscitur, per
                        <rs key="#Landed_possessions">fines</rs> hic subscriptas: qualiter vadit <rs key="#Rivers"
                            >fluvius</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/2323">Sangro</placeName> versum qua
                        parte Rasinus fluit, et exinde decurrit rivus, qui exit de Quinque Milia
                        usque in Petra, ubi fuit <rs key="#Castle">antiquitus castellum</rs>, et
                        quomodo tota ipsa vallis vadit in <rs key="#Rivers">rivo</rs> de <placeName
                            key="#Rivers">Camarda</placeName> , et ipse rivus decurrit in fluvius
                        Sangro; 
                        
                        atque <rs key="#Churches">ecclesiam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Churches #Landed_possessions" ref="#juridical_persons/2302">Sancti
                            Marcelli</orgName>, propinqua <placeName key="#Churches #Landed_possessions"
                            ref="#places/2822">Pectorano</placeName> cum omnibus rebus ibidem
                        subiacentibus: que quoniam ecclesias, et cellas
                        , et curtes ipsi Sancte iuste
                        cognovimus pertinere Ecclesie, hac nostra preceptali auctoritate eidem
                        monasterio et Sancte Ecclesie <rs key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">restituimus et reddimus</rs> ipsas ecclesias, et
                        cellas, et curtes una cum omni eorum integritate, terris, <rs key="#Wine">vineis</rs>, pratis,
                        <rs key="#Animals #Hay/fodder">pascuis</rs>, <rs key="#Forests">silvis</rs>, <rs key="#Fisheries #Fish">piscacionibus</rs>
                            , <rs key="#Rivers #Riverbed">aquis, rivis</rs>, <rs key="#Mills">molendinis</rs>, omnibusque rebus
                        ad ipsas ecclesias, et cellas, et curtes pertinentibus, quatenus per hoc
                        nostre auctoritatis preceptum habeat ipsum monasterium easdem ecclesias, et
                        cellas, et curtes cum eorum omni integritate, habeantque potestatem
                        prenominatus abbas, suique successores quicquid ad utilitatem ecclesie eis
                        rectum visum fuerit faciendi, omnium hominum contradiccione remota. Si quis
                        vero dux, princeps, marchio, comes, seu aliqua nostri regni inferior aud
                        superior persona deinceps perscriptas ecclesias, et cellas, et curtes, aut
                        pertinencias eorum ad prelibata Sancti Vincencii ecclesia tollere
                        presumpserit, et hoc nostrum preceptum infregerit, cognoscat se compositurum
                        auri optimi libras centum, medietatem Camere nostre, et medietatem
                        pretextato abbati, suisque successoribus. Quod ut verius credatur et
                        diligencius ab omnibus observetur, hanc paginam exinde conscribi et propria
                        manu roborantes, subtus insigniri iussimus. Signum domni Ottonis serenissimi
                        imperatoris et invictissimi augusti. <persName key="#Chancellor"><name
                                ref="Iohannes">Iohannes</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs>, ad vicem [...] <persName
                            key="#Bishops #Archchancellor"><name ref="Petrus"
                            >Petri</name></persName> [...] <rs key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Archchancellor">archicancellarii</rs>, recognovi et subscripsi.
                            <date>Data .VI. idus octubris, anno Dominice incarnacionis .DCCCCLXXXI.,
                            imperii vero domni secundi Ottonis .XIIII., indiccione .X. Actum
                                <placeName key="#Palatium" ref="#places/110">Beneventi</placeName>,
                            in <rs key="#Palatium">palacio</rs></date>, in Dei nomine, feliciter,
                        amen.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
